HEADWORD: Syngnathi
<hw>Syng"na*thi</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>sy`n</grk> with + <?/ jaw.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
suborder of lophobranch fishes which have an elongated snout and lack
the ventral and first dorsal fins. The pipefishes and sea horses are
examples.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Syng"na*thous</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

